         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Chief Secretary's Office ¶ 21st May 1870 ¶ Memo. ¶  ¶ With reference to Dr. Mueller's note of yesterday's date ¶  inclosing letter to the Editor of "The Argus" I am desired by the Chief Secretary to c...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.05.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 1225, unit 20, p. 1, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21st May 1870</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Memo.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With reference to Dr. Mueller's note of yesterday's date<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Odgers, 20 May 1870.</p>
               </note> inclosing letter to the Editor of "The Argus" I am desired by the Chief Secretary to call Dr. Mueller's attention to the 21st. Civil Service Regulation and to say that Sir Jas. McCulloch considers that officers had far better devote themselves to the duties of their offices and not to newspaper correspondence.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am further to point out that all communications to this Department on Public Business should be by official letter to the Chief Secretary</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Director</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanic Gardens</p>
         </div>
      </body>
